issue.title: DML EP QuantizeLinear defer axis validation for test_quantizelinear_cpu

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
**Description**: Defer validating the `axis` attribute until later. Even though the actual model file is otherwise identical, evidently ONNX behavior changed and now always returns `axis` = 1 even when the attribute doesn't actually exist in the model file; and since the tensor is 1D, the DML EP validation failed as axis 1 >= rank 1.

**Motivation and Context**
- *Why is this change required? What problem does it solve?* ONNX 1.12 backend test cases are failing, as ORT just updated to ONNX 1.12.
- *If it fixes an open issue, please link to the issue here.* https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/11902

body:
@fdwr because `y_scale` is a scalar, `axis` should be ignored:

From the [spec](https://github.com/onnx/onnx/blob/main/docs/Operators.md#QuantizeLinear):

> axis : int (default is 1)
(Optional) The axis of the quantization dimension of the input tensor. Ignored for per-tensor quantization.

And per-tensor quantization is indicated by a scalar value of `y_scale`:

> y_scale : tensor(float)
Scale for doing quantization to get 'y'. It can be a scalar, which means per-tensor/layer quantization, or a 1-D Tensor for per-axis quantization.

So the EP should not be checking `axis` in this case.
